## <a id="prerequisites"></a>Prerequisites

### <a id="virtualbox"></a>VirtualBox

PCF Dev uses [VirtualBox](https://www.virtualbox.org) version 5.0 and above as its virtualizer.

1. Download VirtualBox 5.0.14 for Windows hosts from [VirtualBox](http://download.virtualbox.org/virtualbox/5.0.14/VirtualBox-5.0.14-105127-Win.exe).

1. Open the `.exe` file and install using the wizard.

### <a id="cf-cli"></a>Cloud Foundry Command Line Interface

PCF Dev uses the [Cloud Foundry Command Line Interface](https://github.com/cloudfoundry/cli) to push and scale apps.

1. To install the cf CLI v6.15.0 for Windows 64 bit, download it from the [cf CLI repo in GitHub](https://cli.run.pivotal.io/stable?release=windows64&version=6.15.0&source=github-rel). If you previously used the cf CLI v5 Ruby gem, uninstall this gem first.

1. Unpack the zip file and open the `cf_installer` application.

1. Follow the installer wizard to install.

1. To verify your installation, open a terminal window and enter `cf`. If your installation was successful, the cf CLI help listing appears.

## <a id="install-pcf-dev"></a>Install PCF Dev

1. Download the latest version of PCF Dev CLI plugin from the [Pivotal Network](https://network.pivotal.io/).
1. Unzip the downloaded zip file.
1. Using PowerShell, navigate to the directory containing the unzipped plugin file.
1. Install the PCF Dev plugin:
<pre class="terminal"> >> cf install-plugin .\pcfdev-VERSION-windows.exe</pre>
1. Start PCF Dev:
<pre class="terminal"> >> cf dev start</pre>

<p class='note'><strong>Note</strong>: You must remove an old version of PCF Dev by running <code>cf uninstall-plugin pcfdev</code> before installing a new version.</p>

## <a id="stopping"></a>Stop PCF Dev
To temporarily stop PCF Dev, run the following command:

<pre class="terminal"> >> cf dev stop</pre>

## <a id="uninstall"></a>Uninstall PCF Dev

To destroy the PCF Dev VM, run the following command:

<pre class="terminal"> >> cf dev destroy</pre>

To remove the PCF Dev cf CLI plugin, run the following command:

<pre class="terminal"> >> cf uninstall-plugin pcfdev</pre>
